		<section>
		<h2>02014-Q1</h2>
		<p>This year we're celebrating randomness. The next four quarters will all have some connection to random and how it plays into our lives, affects us and our actions.</p>
		<div class="banner"><img src="contest/2014-Q1-header.jpg" alt="Fooled by randomness by Nassim Nicholas Taleb"/></div>
		<p>We're clearing off the bookshelf with our collection of random books. Our first book this year is Nassim Nicholas Taleb's Fooled by Randomness. It is a great companion for those who've read Black Swan.</p>
	</section>

	<section>
			<p><strong>Here's how to win:</strong> You need to send us your latitude and longitude by moving and zooming the map so the cross-hairs are centered close to your location. The lat/lon is used to randomly pick the winner and the email address is so we can contact you. That's it. You don't need to spam 6 friends or retweet or follow us. The only thing we ask in return is that you subscribe the <a href="newsletter/index.html">mailing list</a>. We send out one single message each quarter and if you don't like it you can unsubscribe after winning, you won't hurt our feelings, well not too much at least.</p>

			<div id="bd">
				<div id="map"></div>
				<div id="crosshair"></div>
			</div>
			<form action="contest.2" method="post"  class="clearfix" style="text-align: center; background-color: #fafafa; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 10px">
				<ul>
					<li>email: <input type="text" name="email" value="" /></li>
					<li>latitude: <input type="text" id="lat" name="lat" value="" /></li>
					<li>longitude: <input type="text" id="lon" name="lon" value="" /></li>
				</ul>
				<input type="submit" name="Submit" value="Enter the contest and subscribe to the mailing list" />

			</form>
			<p><strong>Note:</strong> If you win, we'll send you an email to get your full address. If your address isn't nearby the lat/lon you sent in, we'll pick a new random point. (So don't get smart and submit 50 times with 50 different locations, then ask us to send it elsewhere.)</p>
	</section>
		<section>

	<p>The winner will be drawn 2 months through the quarter and contacted directly, then announced via the newsletter. The submitted point closest to the randomly chosen point, according to the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haversine_formula">Haversine Formula</a> will be deemed the winner.</p>

	</section>

